  "response": "The shortest completed Test match in terms of time is the match between Australia and South Africa at Melbourne, which took place in February 1932. This match ended in just 656 overs, lasting a total of 656 minutes (approximately 11 hours). In terms of days, it was completed in just 2 days. South Africa batted for only 60.3 overs in their first innings and 66.3 overs in their second innings, and Australia managed to conclude the match with their innings in a similarly quick fashion. This remains a notable record in the history of cricket.",
